modules.name: AWS.CUR
modules.comments: All public APIs for AWS Cost and Usage Report service

declarations.comments: Describe a list of report definitions owned by the account
declarations.title: describeReportDefinitions

declarations.comments: Enable support for Redshift and/or QuickSight.
declarations.title: AdditionalArtifact

declarations.comments: A message indicates if the deletion is successful.
declarations.title: DeleteResponseMessage

declarations.comments: This exception is thrown when putting a report preference with a name that already exists.
declarations.title: DuplicateReportNameException

declarations.comments: A message to show the detail of the exception.
declarations.title: ErrorMessage

declarations.comments: This exception is thrown on a known dependency failure.
declarations.title: InternalErrorException

declarations.comments: The max number of results returned by the operation.
declarations.title: MaxResults

declarations.comments: The definition of AWS Cost and Usage Report. Customer can specify the report name, time unit, report format, compression format, S3 bucket and additional artifacts and schema elements in the definition.
declarations.title: ReportDefinition

declarations.comments: This exception is thrown when the number of report preference reaches max limit. The max number is 5.
declarations.title: ReportLimitReachedException

declarations.comments: Preferred name for a report, it has to be unique. Must starts with a number/letter, case sensitive. Limited to 256 characters.
declarations.title: ReportName

declarations.comments: Preferred report path prefix. Limited to 256 characters.
declarations.title: S3Prefix

declarations.comments: Preference of including Resource IDs. You can include additional details about individual resource IDs in your report.
declarations.title: SchemaElement

declarations.comments: The frequency on which report data are measured and displayed.
declarations.title: TimeUnit

declarations.comments: This exception is thrown when providing an invalid input. eg. Put a report preference with an invalid report name, or Delete a report preference with an empty report name.
declarations.title: ValidationException
